					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Could an IRQ or NMI be firing when you don't expect it, and the handler switching banks out from under you (and not restoring them when the handler exits)?
<br />
<br />Are your IRQs and NMIs disabled when the MMC1 bank switch routine is actually running (or at least, timed to not occur then)?
<br />
<br />In my MMC1 experiment, I store the bank's number at $bfff.  My NMI handler saves that on the stack (lda, pha), and on NMI exit, it checks to see if the bank has changed, and if so, restores it.  But I don't have code to prevent an NMI during the MMC1 switcher (I was no where near close to running over my CPU budget, so it wasn't a problem yet).</div>

